RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 1, 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAX broke a step slow and rounded the opening turn about the three path, started a bid toward the seven sixteenths pole, steadily improved from that point, raced in the four path of the far turn, dug in for the lead past the sixteenth pole and drew clear later yards. CENTERFOLD ANGEL took the lead two deep leaving the three quarter pole and rated the pace inside, came under pressure past the three eighths, raced at the rail on the far turn, was met past the sixteenth pole and relented later yards. MISS WILD stalked three wide, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the stretch. SOCIAL EXCLUSION raced five wide on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, came through the far turn about the five path and raced evenly in the lane. EMMA AND I saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and showed little further. SO RED THE ROSE took a brief early lead, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. ONEPRETTYTHING raced four wide on the opening turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened into the far turn. TIZBIT showed little response. LIGHTFOOT MISS saved ground. SEEDS OF TIME raced well off the pace and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Centerfold Angel
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Shake and Bake Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Sax
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow break,3p 1st turn,bid 7/16,4p far turn,up past 1/16,clr

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARIBBEAN PLEASURE exchanged contact with Golden Adage leaving the gate, gave chase inside and held aim at the rail through the turn, eased just to the outside of. MR. COMMANDER entering the stretch, dug in for the lead later yards and raced clear under the wire. The latter was hustled along the opening furlong and took over approaching the three eighths pole, contested the rail on the turn, dug in under steady stretch encouragement but was met in later yards and relented nearing the wire. YO VINNIE gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn then dueled through the final sixteenth for third. ISRAELI ARMY chased through the backstretch, raced at the rail on the turn then eased out entering the stretch and was outfinished for third the final sixteenth. GOLDEN ADAGE exchanged contact with Caribbean Pleasure leaving the gate, gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. GREAT GOOGLYMOOGLY pressured the pace approaching the three eighths pole, dropped back off the rail toward the quarter then flattened leaving the turn. PERSONAL FINANCE pressured the pace nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the turn in the four path and weakened in the lane. ANNIE'S KINGDOM was not a factor and rounded the turn about the five path. THE CLOWN pressured the pace nearing the three eighths pole but weakened in the five path on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Caribbean Pleasure
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,chased inside,rail turn,up late,clear wire

ENTRY.NAME: Great Googlymoogly
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FULL MOON LOVER exchanged contact with Emberly leaving the gate then closed to the front approaching the seven sixteenths pole and dueled Jacks Sister Jill from that point, edged clear at the rail midway on the turn and was all out to hold on. COACH RUBE was forced outward on the chute then gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn, dug in from the head of the lane and finished well while gaining on the winner. MANAROLA chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and dueled clear for third in later yards. JACKS SISTER JILL dueled Full Moon Lover leaving the seven sixteenths pole but dropped back while losing ground through the turn and flattened stride the final sixteenth. JUBA'S HOUSE gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. MISS WAVE chased outside, rounded the turn about the six path and showed little in the lane. EMBERLY exchanged contact with Full Moon Lover leaving the gate, gave chase inside but faded toward the five sixteenths pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Full Moon Lover
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 1 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANGE THE WORLD rated close two deep on the opening turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and entered the far turn near the rail, eased out to come between horses into the stretch, took the lead past the eighth pole, dueled clear mid-stretch and held on well. THE SKY IS FALLING saved ground on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path, closed to a clear second in later yards and was gaining on the winner. CHROMATIC LASS moved to the inside and rated the pace, was met by Cousin Winner at the seven sixteenths pole but recovered the advantage approaching the five sixteenths, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, gave up the lead past the eighth pole and flattened stride the final sixteenth. HESSICA rated close in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced close in the four path on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. COUSIN WINNIE stalked the early pace two deep, took a slim lead at the seven sixteenths pole but was met approaching the five sixteenths, dropped back midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. TIMETOGETUP raced close to the early pace inside then gave chase leaving the first turn, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: The Sky Is Falling
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,5p far turn,finished well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 15200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 1, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCAPTURED KING rated close inside, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole but lacked room at the rail leaving the five sixteenths, eased four wide approaching the top of the lane, dueled to the lead mid-stretch and drew away the final sixteenth. FLAT CAT stalked four wide on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, took over in the three path approaching the quarter, was met mid-stretch and flattened the final sixteenth. HPNOTIQ RHYTHM raced off the rail on the opening turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened into the far turn. SPRING THE BEAST showed little response through the backstretch. MAKE WAY came away awkwardly and was shuffled back early then saved ground.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOVE OF GRACE stalked two deep, started a bid leaving the five sixteenths pole and took over two deep midway on the far turn, dueled clear into the lane and held well under steady handling. LUCKY BOP stalked three wide on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, entered the far turn about the six path and finished well to clear second later yards. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 31500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners O f A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since May 1 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIVINE FASHION rated close inside, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole and raced close in the three path of the far turn, dug in for the lead inside the sixteenth pole and drew clear later yards. SENECA ROCKS moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole and kept the edge over CASTLE OF CAYLEE through the backstretch, contested even terms at the rail midway on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for second. The latter stalked two deep, challenged at the seven sixteenths pole and dueled to even terms midway on the far turn, but was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. BACKSTREET AFFAIR settled off the pace about the three path, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly down the lane. GRACE'S SECRET settled off the pace in the four and five paths, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened in the three path on the far turn. BREADMAN'S ROSEBUD settled off the pace in the two and three paths, had her heels clipped into the second turn and showed little response through the backstretch. KATALIMA saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened into the far turn. STAR RULES raced inside through the front stretch, came out a path and made contact with EX RATED approaching the five eighths pole and proved no factor while saving ground. The latter raced well off the pace just off the rail, was forced out and clipped the heels of Breadman's Rosebud approaching the five eighths pole and lost her rider. The Stewards reviewed the incident into the second turn before declaring this race official.

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Fashion
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,bid 5/16,3p far turn,up past 1/16,clear late

ENTRY.NAME: Seneca Rocks
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 7/16,edge rail far turn,dueled 2nd

RACE.FOOTNOTES: POLISH THE DIAMOND chased through the backstretch and raced close three wide on the turn, dug in for the lead in later yards and raced clear under the wire. PHANTOM QUEEN set a pressured early pace most of the opening quarter mile then prompted the issue past the three eighths pole, contested at near even terms two deep on the turn and dueled through the stretch for second. KNOBIESMAGICSONDE closed to the lead past the three eighths pole and set a pressured pace inside, contested the edge at the rail on the turn but was met in later yards then outfinished for second. LUZIA chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and passed rivals in the duel through the stretch. GHOST OF ALCINA gave chase, raced in the three and four path on the turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. VERY VENUS chased, raced two deep on the turn and showed little in the lane. SMOKIN LADY engaged in close chase through the backstretch, remained a factor in the three path on the turn but was eased to the outside entering the stretch and weakened. LIL BOUGIE chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn and weakened. RUMORGOINGAROUND came away a step slow and was shut off leaving the gate. CARMELIZED was taken up shortly after the break and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Luzia
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,passed rivals in stretch duel

ENTRY.NAME: Smokin Lady
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
